{"name":"Alchemy","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 29\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To practice the sorcery-science of alchemy. Apprentice <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">illusionists </span>learn how to identify potions by taste alone; albeit the practice is not always safe. At 7th level, an <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">illusionist</span> may concoct potions with the assistance of an alchemist. By 11th level, the assistance of an alchemist is no longer required. For more information, refer to <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>alchemy</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579237902,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"E094Eg21uCsgWcyE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Dexterity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of dexterity</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>dexterity</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E094Eg21uCsgWcyE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"TW0YJlsRZMN0GyDg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scrolls with spells from the <strong>I<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">llusionist</span>&nbsp;Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 95</strong>), unless the scroll was created by an ecclesiastical sorcerer (one who casts cleric or druid spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"bX3YTqJf9MaW8cWV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Illusionists cast spells that they memorize from arcane tomes. They also channel strange energies from darkness, light, and sound. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 34</strong>, though illusionists of high intelligence gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>intelligence</em>). For example, a 4th-level illusionist with 13 intelligence can cast four level 1 spells and two level 2 spells per day.</p>\n<p>The illusionist begins with a spell book that contains three level 1 spells drawn from the <strong>Illusionist Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>Table 95</em>). Through personal research, illusionists develop one new spell at each level gain; this spell is learnt automatically, with no need of a qualification roll, but it must be of a castable level (see <strong>Table 34</strong>).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;3</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;1</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251346735,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"byylCQz9KuaDNJJc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Read Magic","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The ability to decipher otherwise unintelligible magical inscriptions or symbols placed on weapons, armour, items, doors, walls, and other media by means of the <em>sorcerer's mark</em> spell or other like methods.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251200032,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"dBdqJBgF9N6KTY9U","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Perceive Illusion","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+2 bonus to saving throws versus illusions and phantasms. If the illusion is that of a sorcerer 3 or more levels lower than the illusionist, then the saving throw bonus is instead equal to the level difference (e.g., a 7th-level illusionist met by the <em>phantasm</em> spell of a 3rd-level bard gains a +4 saving throw bonus).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E094Eg21uCsgWcyE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"jXCCRVP7MBoxY14L","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Vizard","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 65\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A cantrap to alter one&rsquo;s countenance by means of a simple illusion. Chin, ears, eyes, hair, lips, nose, teeth, and all such facial features can be altered, including shape, colour, thickness, blemishes, and so forth. The illusionist must touch his or her face for one round (10 seconds) and imagine the desired features. The vizard is only detectable if a viewer peers closely (within 12 inches of face) or casts <em>detect phantasm</em>. Otherwise, the effect lasts for 1 turn (10 minutes) and may be executed once per day from 1st to 6th level, twice per day from 7th to 12th level. Regardless of level, any illusionist can see through another illusionist&rsquo;s <em>vizard</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bX3YTqJf9MaW8cWV"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"olvgtLwWDPxd1rn2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Coloured Globe","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 64\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Once per day per level of experience, evoke a 6-inch diameter <em>coloured globe</em> to rise from the open palm and float within 10 feet, as directed by the illusionist. A <em>coloured globe</em> glows any pastel colour as chosen by the illusionist, shedding light in a 10-foot radius. It lasts 6 turns (1 hour) with no need of concentration. Multiple coloured globes can be simultaneously controlled if so desired.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E094Eg21uCsgWcyE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579237902,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"rb5amtbOdnwjp3dE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials may include the finest vellum, paper, or papyrus; a fresh quill; and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"illusionist","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579237903,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"vpzZSC5iVhiN8Wam","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
